overview: The user wanted to make their sleep questionnaire app look more
  beautiful and less generic. The agent started by analyzing the existing
  design, identifying areas like the color palette, typography, spacing, form
  elements, and overall visual interest as needing improvement. A new, calming
  sleep-themed color palette was introduced, and the main form layout was
  redesigned with subtle background elements and an improved progress indicator.
  The welcome screen was transformed with a hero section and feature cards, and
  all core UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards
  received a polished, consistent look. Crucially, the agent systematically
  applied these new styles across all 14 questionnaire sections, replacing old
  gray boxes with refined card-style groupings and updating typography. During
  the review, a console error related to  values being passed to input
  fields was identified and fixed by modifying the  component to safely
  handle such values. The result is a more professional, cohesive, and
  aesthetically pleasing application that aligns with a sleep health theme.
